  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Continuity Constraint.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\partial_r(rv_r)+\\partial_z(zv_z)=0.\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Resonance Operator.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathcal{R}_{\\mathrm{EHD}}[\\mathbf{v}]\n=\n-\\frac{\\nabla p}{\\rho}\n+\n\\frac{q}{m}\n(\\mathbf{E}+\\mathbf{v}\\times\\mathbf{B}).\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Mode Selection.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathcal{R}_{\\mathrm{EHD}}[\\mathbf{v}_k]\n=\n\\lambda_k\\mathbf{v}_k.\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nThe admissible axisymmetric flow space is constrained by:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\partial_r(rv_r)+\\partial_z(zv_z)=0.\n\\end{equation}\n\nPressure and electromagnetic forcing define the total acceleration operator:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathcal{R}_{\\mathrm{EHD}}[\\mathbf{v}]\n=\n-\\frac{\\nabla p}{\\rho}\n+\n\\frac{q}{m}\n(\\mathbf{E}+\\mathbf{v}\\times\\mathbf{B}).\n\\end{equation}\n\nResonant modes are those reproduced by the operator up to scale:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n\\mathcal{R}_{\\mathrm{EHD}}[\\mathbf{v}_k]\n=\n\\lambda_k\\mathbf{v}_k.\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nThe EHD resonance operator identifies flow modes amplified by pressure and electromagnetic forcing.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
